<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/908917559e5db3aab95ef7835082d2e4.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 5 and A = 50 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>4.2</li><li>6.5</li><li>40.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({50}\right)}}}=\frac{{5}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{5}}{{\tan{{\left({50}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{4.1954981558864}\approx{4.2}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={5}^{{2}}+{4.1954981558864}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={25}+{17.602204776046}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={42.602204776046}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{42.602204776046}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{6.5270364466614}\approx{6.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{50}^{\circ}\approx{40}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

